# Whitelist .gitignore: ignore everything by default, explicitly allow only the files
# that belong in the repo. When you add a new file type, add it to the allowlist below.

# ─── Step 1: ignore everything ────────────────────────────────────────────────
*

# ─── Step 2: allow git to descend into directories ────────────────────────────
# Without these, git won't look inside subdirectories at all, and the allowlist
# below can never match nested files.
!*/
!.github/

# ─── Step 3: allowlist (essential file types and specific filenames) ──────────

# Repo metadata
!.gitignore
!.gitattributes
!.editorconfig

# Project / build configuration
!*.toml
!*.lock

# Documentation and license
!*.md
!LICENSE
!LICENSE.*

# Source
!*.rs

# CI workflows
!*.yml
!*.yaml

# Future: WiX MSI installer sources (the Windows Service host, CP2)
!*.wxs
!*.wxi
!*.wxl

# Static assets shipped with the repo (logos, diagrams)
!*.png
!*.jpg
!*.jpeg
!*.svg
!*.webp

# ─── Step 4: re-ignore noise that the allowlist would otherwise let through ───
# These run last so they override anything matched above.

# Rust build artifacts
target/
*.pdb
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# OS junk
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Local config / secrets (overrides !*.toml for the *.local.toml case)
.env
.env.*
*.local.toml
/secrets/

# Agent runtime state — holds this machine's identity key + session token.
# (JSON isn't in the allowlist, so it's already ignored; explicit + documented
# here because leaking it would expose the machine's credentials.)
sylva-agent-state.json
